-- Fazer Group Russian Subsidiary’s General Director Leaves Company
-- B y   A n a t o l y   T e m k i n
-- 2012-05-30T11:40:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-30/fazer-group-russian-subsidiary-s-general-director-leaves-company.html
Fazer Group’s Russian manager is
stepping down, the Finnish baked-goods company said in a
statement.  Daniil Briman, the general director of the St. Petersburg,
Russia-based subsidiary  OAO Khlebny dom , will be replaced by
Financial Director Sergei Popov, the company said today.  Briman, who was appointed in February 2011, was previously
a vice president for OAO Baltika, the Russian brewer owned by
 Carlsberg AS. (CARLB)  He will continue his career in another field, the
statement said, without providing details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anatoly Temkin in St. Petersburg at 
 atemkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  